"{\"uid\": \"gbnews.com-sport-tennis-andy-murray-confirms-retire-after-olympics\", \"text\": \"Andy Murray has confirmed he will be retiring from tennis after the Paris Olympics  PA  ByJack Otway,  Published: 23/07/2024  The 37-year-old is poised to walk away from the sport after a glittering career  Fans on social media have flooded Andy Murray with messages of support after he confirmed he'd be retiring from tennis after the Paris Olympics.  It was already an open secret that the former world No 1 would be walking off into the sunset once this summer's prestigious event is out of the way.  And Murray, writing on X, has now confirmed the news everybody was expecting to hear.\\\"Arrived in Paris for my last ever tennis tournament @Olympics,\\\" he wrote.Arrived in Paris for my last ever tennis tournament@OlympicsCompeting for \\ud83c\\uddec\\ud83c\\udde7 have been by far the most memorable weeks of my career and I am extremely proud to get do it one final time!pic.twitter.com/keqnpvSEE1- Andy Murray (@andy_murray)July 23, 2024\\\"Competing for [Great Britain] have been by far the most memorable weeks of my career and I am extremely proud to get do it one final time!\\\"Murray has been flooded with messages of support from fans, with many hoping to see him win Olympic gold.\\\"Best of luck man, perfect way to end a legendary career,\\\" were the words of one user.\\\"Good luck Andy. You have been inspirational for new generation. Respect to you,\\\" said a second.JUST IN:England next manager: Four candidates dismissed as Gareth Southgate replacement hunt continuesA third stated: \\\"Good luck Andy. Bring it home.\\\"Another said: \\\"You are such a wonderful tennis player and role model. Your dedication and especially your success (Grand Slams, Olympic gold) make you a true inspiration.\\\"A fifth praised Murray by saying: \\\"Enjoy, you deserve to, for all you have done for British tennis!\\\"And a sixth fan said: \\\"Best of luck! We are all with you.\\\"READ MORE: